1
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,120
A bit stunned.

2
00:00:06,120 --> 00:00:07,040
Liu.

3
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:09,880
Are you sure it's not an echo?

4
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:10,960
What?

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:11,480
Just a sec.

6
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:17,000
I can't... I can't look.

7
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:21,920
It's really him!

8
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,520
- He is here!
- Oh, my!

9
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,520
That was seriously cool.

10
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:28,960
So magnetic!

11
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:34,400
For real?

12
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,040
For real.

13
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:40,720
So that was you calling me just now?

14
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:48,040
(No one's cutting in line on my watch.)

15
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:50,360
I'm here to take you out
for a late-night bite.

16
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,480
Really?

17
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:58,880
(How is he not even flinching?)

18
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:00,640
Late-night snacks for you.

19
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:03,720
Hello.

20
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:06,840
Hi.

21
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:07,520
I'm Zhou Youling.

22
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,400
I'm Ling Lizheng.

23
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,600
I just wrapped up over there, so...

24
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,280
And you...

25
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:17,000
(This happened earlier with BK and...)

26
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,120
Hello. Together?

27
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:19,480
Okay. I'll just watch.

28
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,200
I'll take her home.

29
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:22,760
"I'll take her home."

30
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:23,880
"Take her home?"

31
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:25,640
I thought it was...

32
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:26,640
Just an echo?

33
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:30,160
Yes. Thought I was hallucinating.

34
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:35,040
That moment right there...
Zhou Youling, you were super forward!

35
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,960
Am I interrupting?

36
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:40,040
Not really.

37
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:41,640
Why didn't you just walk in?

38
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:44,840
Just teasing her.

39
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,520
Serves you right for getting asked out
by five girls.

40
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:00,640
(The pressure is immense.)

41
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,720
(Sweat's pouring down both sides.)

42
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:04,080
(New guest on one side,
Zhou Youling on the other.)

43
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,160
(At that moment, I felt...)

44
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:07,160
I didn't even know where to look.

45
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,400
I just stayed silent.

46
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,080
Too afraid to look up.
I just stared at the ukulele.

47
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,680
(Another male guest)

48
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,400
(suddenly joined us.)

49
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:18,720
First, I was a bit surprised.

50
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,440
But it made sense to me.

51
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,600
I have faith in my taste.

52
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,680
And

53
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,720
for the person I like,

54
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,640
(there could be other pursuers.)

55
00:02:26,640 --> 00:02:27,280
(That was)

56
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:29,280
not unexpected.

57
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,520
I think things got more interesting.

58
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,360
Things got interesting.

59
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,480
So your task for today

60
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,440
is to escort her back?

61
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:40,800
Yes, after you're done.

62
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,040
Obviously, you have to wait
until we finish.

63
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:43,480
- Right?
- Oh, my!

64
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,360
If I were Liu,

65
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,520
my dopamine levels would be
off the charts by now.

66
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,080
Of course, I'll wait.

67
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,680
How long have you been at it?

68
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,320
Well... Didn't really track the time.

69
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,600
Honestly, not too long.

70
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,360
How did you know I was here?

71
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:12,240
I was told to come here.

72
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,920
I got to the basement.

73
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:19,000
And I learned there was a sudden change.

74
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,960
Naughty.

75
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:23,960
What do you mean?

76
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,560
She had a date with me today.

77
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,080
Then I got word that

78
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,680
a new male guest was coming.

79
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,280
I got cut off.

80
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,080
That's it.

81
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,920
I know every single shop here, you know?

82
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,640
You stole my date,

83
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:37,120
and can't I steal it back?

84
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,600
So you found us yourself?

85
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,560
I live right next door.

86
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,600
Either it's a live house,

87
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,520
or

88
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,520
this craft shop.

89
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,480
Or downstairs, the dancing place.

90
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,560
I figured you wouldn't be dancing.

91
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,160
Why not? It's possible.

92
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:49,560
Do you dance too?

93
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,640
(This is intense.)

94
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:52,480
No.

95
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,360
(Heading back to the house)
Driver,

96
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,960
back to that parking lot just now.

97
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:02,760
(Just then,)

98
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,120
(I hadn't processed it yet.)

99
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,360
(I decided to just go back.)

100
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:08,200
Starting the U-turn back,

101
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:08,960
I figured

102
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:11,760
I couldn't come for nothing.

103
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,160
So I turned back around

104
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:14,960
and went to find them.

105
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,960
That's a bit too macho.

106
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:20,880
It goes on the string...

107
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,520
Wait, if it's on the string,
you probably can't even pluck it anymore.

108
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,280
(At that moment, I just wanted)

109
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,560
(to see what they were up to.)

110
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,960
I didn't want to disturb their date.

111
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,000
I was actually hiding in the back,

112
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,480
planning to observe first.

113
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:36,040
But the two of them looked

114
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,040
pretty happy.

115
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,240
So I called out from back there.

116
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:40,840
I called out a couple of times.

117
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,080
Liu.

118
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:44,960
Liu.

119
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:45,560
It's just...

120
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,960
How do I put this...
Probably because my date got sniped.

121
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,720
I'm not feeling too great
about it, honestly.

122
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,640
Even though it's understandable,

123
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,480
I'm still not feeling too great.

124
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,440
And today...

125
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,040
What is it?

126
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,040
Today was very eventful.

127
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,480
It happened twice today.

128
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,000
What do you mean?

129
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,560
There were two new male guests.

130
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,680
- There were two today?
- Yeah, besides you, there was another.

131
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:09,720
It was also him?

132
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,720
It was all him.

133
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,960
But he is Mr. Popular,

134
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,440
so...

135
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:20,200
My apologies!

136
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,480
I bought some snacks.

137
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:31,760
We can share them back at the house.

138
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,320
You guys keep painting.

139
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,440
Message me when you're done.

140
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:35,880
Alright.

141
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,400
I'll go take a stroll.

142
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,480
Okay.

143
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:41,879
(Oh, my God.)

144
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,440
(Couldn't calm down for a long time.)

145
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,560
Hope he walks slowly,

146
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,160
takes some time.

147
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,680
And the way he handled that was perfect.

148
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:55,440
- He just left.
- He left first to let the two talk.

149
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,520
- Yeah.
- Anyway, it'll be him taking her home.

150
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,160
I felt so awkward sitting there,

151
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,200
watching the two of them on their date,

152
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,960
doing crafts.

153
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:07,440
I sitting there watching
wasn't right. Right?

154
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,680
If I stayed there,

155
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,800
they couldn't focus either.

156
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,360
So I said I'd go take a walk

157
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,640
to let them finish.

158
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Do you two usually interact quite a bit?

159
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:20,680
Yeah.

160
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,400
That's a secret.

161
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:23,520
- It's a secret?
- Yeah, secret.

162
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:25,880
Reconnaissance on the enemy.

163
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:26,800
Yes.

164
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,120
Your secrets are written on your face.

165
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:34,240
His name is Zhou Youling, right?

166
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,480
Yes, Zhou Youling.

167
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,360
"You" for blessing,
"ling" for ice cream.

168
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:39,960
"Ling" for ice cream.

169
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,840
Silence fell.

170
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,720
Silence.

171
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,040
No, just felt it was weird.

172
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,880
Let me think.

173
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,320
Can I add some elements

174
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,360
to your name, "Liu"?

175
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:57,440
Try it.

176
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,000
Any ideas?

177
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:00,960
- Because...
- Tough question, huh?

178
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:03,000
My surname is also "Ling" for Ice Cream.

179
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,440
Really?

180
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,520
"Ling" for Soar High Among the Clouds.

181
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,560
"My name includes the same character."

182
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,720
"And his, too."

183
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,200
Which kind are you looking for?

184
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:12,920
(I think)

185
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,000
(you could clearly sense)

186
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,480
(that Zhou Youling)

187
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,280
(was interested in Xu Lvyang.)

188
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,000
While signing it,

189
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,320
I just played along,

190
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:21,600
seizing the moment.

191
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,040
I just wanted her

192
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,080
(to remember me a bit more vividly too.)

193
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,800
(There was this sense of competition.)

194
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,920
That was rather intense.

195
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,280
They both tried pretty hard.

196
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,440
Yes, both going for it aggressively.

197
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,600
Wait, I think I have an idea!

198
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,160
I got it!

199
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,960
Wind through willow leaves.

200
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:52,840
You have quite the talent.

201
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,680
Really!

202
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,280
You really provide
a lot of emotional gratification.

203
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:56,840
Fated match.

204
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:57,960
It looks genuinely great.

205
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,360
(Neither of them intends to leave.)

206
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,280
(Neither intends to back down.)

207
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,200
What's that about?

208
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,800
What I meant to say was

209
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,400
you rush in like a fierce wind.

210
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,280
(A razor wind slicing through willow leaves)
It slices through.

211
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,680
Why do you feel that?

212
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,080
Your features.

213
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,920
Love it, perfect, thank you.

214
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,440
Hope I didn't ruin it.

215
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,880
- Hope I didn't ruin it.
- Alright. I felt good today.

216
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,960
You could just soak up some water.

217
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:28,960
The domineering CEO is back at it again.

218
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:30,000
Domineering CEO.

219
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,440
Welcome back.

220
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:33,120
Have you done?

221
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,520
Almost there.

222
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:41,120
Did you add extras?

223
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,040
I added just a bit of color.

224
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:43,600
Because I thought

225
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,720
it needed a touch of green.

226
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,760
Because your core...

227
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,240
Feels a bit stronger?

228
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:48,880
True.

229
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,160
Happy times fly by so fast.

230
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,520
We have plenty of time left together.

231
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:58,680
So,

232
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:00,920
the good times

233
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:01,920
won't end today.

234
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,240
Go. You already bought food?

235
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,680
Yeah, I bought some snacks for all.

236
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,520
Stir-fried choy sum.

237
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,680
And cherry tomatoes.

238
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,520
See how they're positioned.

239
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,680
The domineering CEO placed himself...

240
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,840
He isn't yielding.

241
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:17,840
He won't step aside.

242
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:25,000
About his action of barging in,

243
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,200
what do we think of that?

244
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,200
(Xia likes it)
Okay.

245
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,720
(Xia Zhiguang)
Imagine

246
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,760
the girl I like is dating someone else,

247
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,040
I wouldn't be happy.

248
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,440
(Evonne agrees too)
Pretty direct and simple.

249
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,080
That's semi-mature age dating.

250
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,200
There's competition and struggle.

251
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,720
I express my feelings.

252
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,040
But I also know when to step back.

253
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:42,800
If I were her,
I'd probably feel a bit smug?

254
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,200
My absolute limit.

255
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,120
The toughest part of my personality.

256
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:51,240
As long as I'm not interrupting them,

257
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,360
(Agitated, and wait)
I'll wait a bit.

258
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,200
What if they happen
to spot you... "Ugh?"

259
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,040
I'd pretend it's a coincidence.

260
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:58,360
I'd say,

261
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,080
"Oh, you two are here too?"

262
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,000
I think the key factor

263
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,720
is whether the girl likes this boy.

264
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,120
If you've sent him a signal,

265
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,200
and he reciprocated,
the chase would be thrilling.

266
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:09,760
Exactly.

267
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:12,560
What's your ultimate killer move
in a relationship?

268
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,000
My killer move is

269
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,240
that when I like someone,

270
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,240
I become very obvious.

271
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,080
"I like whatever you like."

272
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:22,280
I'll

273
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,040
become a different person.

274
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,520
Zhisheng.

275
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:26,800
(Let me think)
What's your killer move?

276
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,120
No.

277
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,840
Maybe we make

278
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,200
lots of deals.

279
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,120
We agreed...

280
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,000
To grow up together.

281
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,520
No, like...

282
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:38,560
Even if we're super mad,

283
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,680
we've got a rule.

284
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,720
